@Lolisniffer True, and while we're at it, let's execute the individuals who initially put in the order for those firearms, and every person who has ever bought one as well. We should probably also kill the other people who create the individual components that make up a gun.

You know what, let's kill the families, friends, and other such individuals of every person who has ever bought a firearm because, if it wasn't for their existence, people probably wouldn't have had nearly as much incentive to buy a firearm.

Do you see where your simplistic, correlative sense of "logic" can take us?
